    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200&deg;C/ 180&deg;C (fan)/ 400&deg;F/ Gas 6</p> <p>Boil a kettle</p> <p>Add the <strong>tortillas</strong> to&nbsp;a large baking tray</p> <p>Place the baking tray in the oven and cook for 4-5 min or until the tortillas are starting to turn brown around the edges</p> <p>Once browned, remove the <strong>tortillas</strong> from the oven and set them aside</p> <p>&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tortizza-margherita-and-rocket-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic </strong></p> <p>Strip the <strong>basil leaves</strong> from their stalks and chop the <strong>stalks</strong> finely, leaving the <strong>leaves</strong> whole for later</p> <p>Combine the <strong>tomato paste</strong> with 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> in a heat-proof bowl</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tortizza-margherita-and-rocket-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> chopped</strong>&nbsp;<strong>garlic, chopped basil stalks, </strong>1 tsp<strong> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> sugar</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>to the bowl &ndash; this is your<strong> tomato sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tortizza-margherita-and-rocket-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, tear the&nbsp;<strong>mozzarella</strong>&nbsp;into large pieces</p> <p>Pat the torn <strong>mozzarella</strong>&nbsp;with kitchen paper, pressing down very firmly so that the mozzarella is nice and dry (this stops your pizzas from being soggy)</p> <p>Cut the <strong>baby&nbsp;plum tomatoes</strong> in half</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tortizza-margherita-and-rocket-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Divide the <strong>tomato sauce</strong> between the&nbsp;<strong>tortillas</strong> and spread it out towards the edges&nbsp;</p> <p>Top with the <strong>torn</strong>&nbsp;<strong>mozzarella</strong>, <strong>basil leaves</strong> and <strong>halved baby plum tomatoes</strong></p> <p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and return to the oven for a further 8-10 min or until the <strong>mozzarella</strong> has fully melted and the <strong>tortillas</strong> are crispy &ndash; these&nbsp;are your <strong>tortizzas</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tortizza-margherita-and-rocket-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice the <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong>&nbsp;finely with a peeler, until you end up with a pile of<strong> cheese shavings</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tortizza-margherita-and-rocket-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash the <strong>wild</strong>&nbsp;<strong>rocket&nbsp;</strong></p> <p>Once the <strong>tort<strong>izzas</strong> </strong>are done,&nbsp;top each one with a handful of the&nbsp;<strong>rocket</strong> and a drizzle of<strong>&nbsp;olive oil</strong></p> <p>Garnish with the <strong>cheese shavings&nbsp;</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tortizza-margherita-and-rocket-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>tort</strong><strong>izzas</strong> into quarters and serve</p> <p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
